Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.30,0:00:04.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A new tragedy occurred in the Mansion of Death.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:05.11,0:00:08.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thee years ago, Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} died there...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:08.13,0:00:12.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And her husband, Akashi Shuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was confined in\None of the rooms of the mansion and died of starvation.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.02,0:00:18.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In his final hours, Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} painted\None of the walls in the room blood red.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:19.24,0:00:21.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What was he trying to say?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.57,0:00:25.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After we started questioning the former residents of the mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.41,0:00:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them, the musician Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, was murdered.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.46,0:00:36.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Similar to Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, he was seated\Non a chair, facing a wall painted red.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:37.59,0:00:40.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A former classmate of Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}, Inspector Morofushi...
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.55,0:00:46.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Went off to investigate alone despite advice\Nfrom another classmate, Inspector Yamato.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.18,0:00:51.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And coming from that Inspector Morofushi was a\Ntext message, with only one sentence written on it.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.35,0:00:54.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"The late Koumei."
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.69,0:00:58.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Moreover, the Mansion of Death was consumed by flames.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.69,0:01:04.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inspector Morofushi was saved by Detective Uehara in a pinch, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.16,0:01:05.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He had been struck in the head, and lost consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:06.45,0:01:08.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As such, we couldn't determine what "the late Koumei" meant...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.87,0:01:11.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And the mystery of the case seemed unfathomable.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.12,0:01:16.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But Ran's unassuming question shed a ray of light on this case.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.13,0:01:18.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which is...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.73,0:01:21.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Love is magic, attack the mystery.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.87,0:01:23.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On Saturday nights, be sure to click on Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:24.35,0:01:26.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're finally nearing the climax...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.34,0:01:28.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's time to unravel the mystery of the Red Wall and the true culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.54,0:01:30.14,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perceiving the one and only truth...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.14,0:01:32.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The appearance of a child and the intellect of an adult...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.02,0:01:34.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,His name is: Detective Conan!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.88,0:03:23.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.42,0:03:28.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This dying message can't be acknowledged\Njust by looking at the red wall alone!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.39,0:03:40.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.10,0:03:42.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So that's why the chairs at the first crime scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.81,0:03:45.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were painted white and black!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.07,0:03:49.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim, Akashi Shuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.11,0:03:51.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was really fond of chess.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:52.99,0:03:57.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If so, why did the culprit leave a red wall at the second crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.08,0:04:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If they did it out of confidence that we'd never find out its meaning...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.80,0:04:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I've got it!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.80,0:04:07.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, the dying message...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.51,0:04:09.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't about the red wall!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.63,0:04:12.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The only person besides the culprit who had to paint it red...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.43,0:04:16.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had to be Naoki Shirou!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.14,0:04:18.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At last...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.14,0:04:23.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At last, you've deduced to this point.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.73,0:04:25.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Koumei?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.98,0:04:28.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You've regained consciousness!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.19,0:04:30.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But is it all right for you to be walking around?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.53,0:04:33.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yes, I'm fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.45,0:04:36.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, let's go catch the culprit!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.16,0:04:40.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mochi drawn on the ground...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.37,0:04:42.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Cannot be consumed.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.17,0:04:47.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's a pity that our deductions are\Nstill like mochi drawn on the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.38,0:04:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't pick it up and have it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.80,0:04:53.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, we lack evidence...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.68,0:04:54.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,However...
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.01,0:04:57.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said it, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.72,0:05:01.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That he would be going to Lecce in Italy soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.02,0:05:04.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And that, if he were gone, that's where we'd need to search.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:09.07,0:05:10.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's most interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.11,0:05:13.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, I have a great idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.66,0:05:14.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As do I.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.45,0:05:18.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey now, you should let headquarters handle this!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.74,0:05:21.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, I cannot allow that.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.16,0:05:22.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, how about this?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.75,0:05:28.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why not type your strategy in one word on your\Ncell phone and then show it to each other?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.80,0:05:33.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like Koumei and Zhou Yu before the Battle of Red Cliffs.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.05,0:05:37.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.05,0:05:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Geez, such a hassle.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.52,0:05:44.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.64,0:05:45.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One, two, and go!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.07,0:05:52.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As I expected...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.15,0:05:55.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the Empty Fort strategy, isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.20,0:06:01.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Please be more considerate, Inspector!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.54,0:06:04.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you keep calling us out like this...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.79,0:06:06.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't do our jobs!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.34,0:06:11.10,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Though it's true we all lived in that mansion before...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:06.88,0:06:11.10,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa Naoki (38)\NActor
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.39,0:06:15.94,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Yamabuki Shouji (39)\NFashion Designer
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.32,0:06:16.81,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The fact that we don't have alibis for\Nlast night must've been coincidental.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.25,0:06:20.44,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The reason why we were at the burning mansion...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.51,0:06:23.11,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Was because we saw that text message, didn't I tell you?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.10,0:06:21.69,Character Card,,0,0,0,,Momose Takuto (37)\NCG Creator
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.77,0:06:26.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,First of all, have you figured out what that red wall's about?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.65,0:06:30.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We haven't worked it out yet...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.61,0:06:36.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But it looks like the second victim,\NNaoki Shirou, did figure out something.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.24,0:06:38.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Do you have any ideas?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.95,0:06:40.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:40.62,0:06:42.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I only knew he needed money.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.58,0:06:46.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But he'd said he'd be traveling soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.83,0:06:48.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.21,0:06:50.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To a place called Lecce in Italy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.09,0:06:58.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In that case, maybe he was about to walk to Lecce,\Nand hide something really important there!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.39,0:07:04.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} said that, if he were\Ngone, that's where we'd need to search.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.31,0:07:07.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why "walk" there?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.39,0:07:10.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because Italy is shaped like a boot, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:10.94,0:07:12.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Whatever!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.90,0:07:16.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you want to keep suspecting us...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.24,0:07:19.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Why don't you find some concrete evidence first?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.57,0:07:21.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We're busy people, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:22.03,0:07:22.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Later.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.79,0:07:24.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Excuse us.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.79,0:07:34.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We've worked hard on this, so why don't you guys wait and see?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.76,0:07:37.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"A journey of a hundred kilometers is only half over after ninety."
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.59,0:07:40.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We cannot lower our guards.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:42.01,0:07:44.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can't throw this race away.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.31,0:07:56.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,PC60, PC60, a taxi robbery occurred in the industry area...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.69,0:08:01.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shit, just as I thought, there are even cops\Nwaiting behind Shirou's apartment...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.49,0:08:05.05,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Did I really fall into a trap?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.08,0:08:06.66,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? A taxi robber?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.45,0:08:08.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Around here?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.54,0:08:10.29,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we have to hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.00,0:08:18.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What? They're leaving?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.01,0:08:21.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that means the apartment's unguarded...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.98,0:08:29.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, wait...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.69,0:08:35.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's a drunkard sitting in front of the apartment, and\Na masked man has been wandering around for a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.02,0:08:39.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,One of them could be a cop.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.65,0:08:41.11,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Mister...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:41.86,0:08:44.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If you sleep here, you'll catch a cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:44.45,0:08:45.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,SHUDDAP!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.74,0:08:47.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,GO AWAY, BRAT!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.33,0:08:50.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn, who does the boss think he is!?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.00,0:08:53.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Maybe I was wrong...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.92,0:08:56.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honey, are you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.34,0:08:58.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You're so drunk.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.26,0:09:02.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Two or three more'll be fine!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.76,0:09:05.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:06.51,0:09:07.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Sowwy...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.35,0:09:10.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ow, ow, owww!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.93,0:09:13.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,My leg's broken!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.02,0:09:14.73,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Honey, you all right?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:16.27,0:09:17.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.69,0:09:19.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Gimme a million yen for medical fees!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.90,0:09:21.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A million?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.90,0:09:23.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I don't have that much money...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:24.41,0:09:26.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then hand over your wallet!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.53,0:09:27.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Noooo...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:27.87,0:09:29.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Extortion?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.54,0:09:34.33,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If the masked man were a cop, he wouldn't turn a blind eye like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.51,0:09:44.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now we can drink some more!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.59,0:09:46.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Are you sure?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.97,0:09:49.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn it...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.52,0:09:53.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What am I gonna tell mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.36,0:09:58.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What!?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:59.23,0:10:01.15,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Don't tell me this guy's...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.15,0:10:02.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A panty thief?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:08.58,0:10:10.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, he's heading for Shiro's room...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.37,0:10:17.35,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Idiot, if he goes in...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.63,0:10:22.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The cops at the front door will...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.26,0:10:25.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,They're gone?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.68,0:10:30.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see, the cops all went after the taxi robber.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:37.52,0:10:40.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That guy just came out of Shiro's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:41.28,0:10:44.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Extortion, panty theft, and burglary...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.57,0:10:47.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,There's no doubt, no cops are around here.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.00,0:10:59.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Now's my chance to find that...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.96,0:11:01.95,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.98,0:11:02.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which one?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.17,0:11:04.76,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Which shoe did he hide it in?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.22,0:11:06.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Perhaps...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.93,0:11:10.60,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,This is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:10.60,0:11:11.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The shoe you're after.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.02,0:11:14.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a unique shoe!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.73,0:11:20.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The heel of the shoe is loose, and there's\Na cell phone memory card inside.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.57,0:11:23.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.90,0:11:27.82,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just like Lecce, the heel of Italy's boot!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.36,0:11:31.53,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a pity, you couldn't find it first...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.20,0:11:34.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Midorikawa Naoki{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.97,0:11:48.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Who are you!?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.22,0:11:50.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Come on, we've met several times already.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.22,0:11:52.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Can't you remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.06,0:11:56.18,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Edogawa Conan...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.18,0:11:57.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A detective.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.06,0:11:58.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You are!?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.48,0:12:02.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But I believe...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:02.27,0:12:03.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You haven't...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.94,0:12:05.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Forgotten about us...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.65,0:12:06.44,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.90,0:12:09.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, that extortion and burglary were...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.28,0:12:11.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.95,0:12:14.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Empty Fort strategy.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.29,0:12:18.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The Empty Fort strategy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.21,0:12:23.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we merely called away the patrol cars, you'd\Nsuspect it was possible a trap had been set.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.42,0:12:28.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If that were your mindset, should we present\Nyou with others around the apartment...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.38,0:12:31.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Acting in a manner the police would not...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.76,0:12:33.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And have them committing a number of crimes...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.30,0:12:37.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Lowering your guard is a simple task.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.66,0:12:42.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,The original Empty Fort strategy was to purposely show vulnerability.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.98,0:12:47.48,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,All in order to make the opposition assume there was\Na hidden trap, causing them to halt their approach.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.89,0:12:50.29,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,But ours has the opposite effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.61,0:12:50.29,title01,,0,0,0,,{\fad(420,0)\shad1\be1}Empty Fort Strategy
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.57,0:12:55.74,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, the reason you police mentioned the boot...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.74,0:13:00.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was to see whether the culprit would\Ncome and fall into your trap, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.75,0:13:05.00,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, we believed from the beginning that you'd come.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.30,0:13:08.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We were intrigued.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.30,0:13:12.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,At the first crime scene, it was the\Nvictim who left the dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:13.26,0:13:17.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yet why did the culprit leave the same\Nmessage at the second crime scene?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.68,0:13:23.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But then, if we consider that the red wall wasn't left by the victim...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.65,0:13:24.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Right.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.15,0:13:30.78,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If we suppose a third person other than the\Nvictim or the culprit painted the wall red...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.82,0:13:37.83,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We can more easily conclude that the culprit duplicated\Nthe scene in order to lead the investigation astray.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.24,0:13:41.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, you're saying this third person was Naoki Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.04,0:13:42.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.67,0:13:48.67,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If someone other than the culprit\Nhad to paint over Akashi's message...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:48.67,0:13:51.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then the message had to have\Nbeen written in katakana as...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.59,0:13:55.89,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"I was killed by Naoki."
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.05,0:13:59.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That means you, Midorikawa Naoki...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.52,0:14:01.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Were his murderer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:01.64,0:14:03.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.10,0:14:08.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That message must've been spotted by Naoki\NShirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} who came to borrow money.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:08.19,0:14:11.61,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He thought that it meant him, so he painted over it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.57,0:14:18.24,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But instead of katakana, why not use kanji to avoid confusion?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:18.24,0:14:19.12,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.74,0:14:22.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He used a spray can to write it, didn't he?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.25,0:14:24.37,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The amount of strokes in kanji would make it blurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.83,0:14:30.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And then, as Shirou{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} painted over it with\Nthat same red spray, he came to a realization.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.17,0:14:36.26,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was that the "Naoki" did not refer to his last name, but rather...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.73,0:14:43.23,Character Card,,0,0,0,,{\fad(960,0)\t(4790,5501,\blur50}Midorikawa Naoki
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.26,0:14:43.22,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To the only person on a first-name basis with\NAkashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} - Midorikawa Naoki san, that was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.85,0:14:50.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then, he took a picture of the partially obscured word\Nwith his cell phone in order to attempt to blackmail you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.77,0:14:51.57,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Isn't that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.28,0:14:54.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah, that's why...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.70,0:14:59.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I killed Shiro in this very room he called me to.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.95,0:15:01.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Damn...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:01.49,0:15:05.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only Shiro hadn't gone to the room Shuusaku was starved in...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.25,0:15:07.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If only I were the one who painted it red...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.42,0:15:10.25,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Could it be, Mister...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.25,0:15:12.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That you still don't get the meaning of the red wall?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.88,0:15:19.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The victim had to get the culprit to paint the\Nwall red to complete his dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:20.30,0:15:22.43,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What do you mean?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.43,0:15:25.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ever heard of "complementary color afterimage"?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.02,0:15:26.52,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Complementary color afterimage?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.93,0:15:30.72,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,If you look elsewhere after staring at one color long enough...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.82,0:15:35.07,Dialogue Top,,0,0,0,,Its complementary color will appear in your visual field.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.57,0:15:35.20,Signs,,0,0,0,,Complementary Color Afterimage?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.53,0:15:40.62,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,See, surgeons always wear light green surgical gowns, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.62,0:15:43.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's because after they keep staring\Nat blood during a long operation...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.91,0:15:49.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Their eyes would form afterimages of green that interfere with\Ntheir focus, so they wear the same color to lessen this effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.54,0:15:56.46,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, the red wall sets up the afterimage\Neffect to show us the real dying message.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.80,0:15:58.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Inside that room...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.55,0:16:04.47,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The fact that the white chair faces the red wall and the black\Nchair faces the white wall while being nailed to the floor...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.47,0:16:07.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Serves as a hint for us to decipher the message.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.52,0:16:11.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Akashi Shuusaku{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} was fond of chess.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.81,0:16:14.27,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In chess, white goes first and then black.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.48,0:16:20.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, it tells us to first sit on the\Nwhite chair and stare at the red wall...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.49,0:16:23.45,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Then sit on the black chair\Nand stare at the white wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.70,0:16:30.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That way, red's complementary color, green,\Nwill vividly appear at the white wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.83,0:16:33.17,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Green...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.17,0:16:35.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning you, Midorikawa{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.51,0:16:38.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's also why Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.55,0:16:42.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Threw all the painting materials out\Nthe window except the red spray.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.60,0:16:46.10,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Just to prevent anyone from painting over it with other colors.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.85,0:16:53.31,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,In other words, he suspected that the first\Nto check on his body might be you...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.31,0:16:56.02,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And whatever he wrote might be removed.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.53,0:17:00.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So he took advantage of that and tried to make you paint over it...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:00.99,0:17:04.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Effectively completing his message that you were the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.83,0:17:10.91,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So it really is like, "The late Koumei scares away the living Zhonda."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:10.91,0:17:11.71,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Precisely.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.13,0:17:19.13,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He tried to make me paint over it, huh...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.34,0:17:22.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What a jerk...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:23.47,0:17:29.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,To think he painted over that important portrait, and\Ncaused the death of such an important person...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.98,0:17:33.06,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,By "portrait," you don't mean...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.06,0:17:33.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Yeah...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.73,0:17:38.36,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It's the one Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} had been looking for\Nbefore succumbing to a heart attack.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.36,0:17:41.86,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,A portrait of Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} that had been\Ncreated by Shuusaku some time ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.41,0:17:46.16,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I found the portrait later on!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.16,0:17:50.08,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was hidden under another portrait I bought last year!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.50,0:17:51.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hidden under?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.58,0:17:56.79,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I bought it because it looked like Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.79,0:17:57.75,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But out of curiosity...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.92,0:18:01.51,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I sent it to be inspected by X-ray.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.51,0:18:06.30,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And it revealed Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s portrait was actually under the layers!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:07.05,0:18:13.77,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That bastard Shuusaku painted over Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}'s portrait\Nwith white, and repainted it with something else!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.94,0:18:16.40,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No way...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.40,0:18:20.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It may be true that Shuusaku's art wasn't\Nfamous until two or three years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.90,0:18:30.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,He may have done that out of desperation, after running\Nlow on money for new supplies like blank canvases...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.58,0:18:33.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But why didn't he tell Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} about it!?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.79,0:18:40.84,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Had he told her about it, Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}\Nwouldn't have died trying to find it!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.92,0:18:45.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Instead, he kept quiet and locked himself\Nin his room to continue painting!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.88,0:18:51.93,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,That's why I trapped him in his room to let him\Ntaste the pain that Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r} had suffered...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:53.52,0:18:55.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,On the day after Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s death...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.02,0:19:05.19,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I came to the mansion, and found a painting burning in the yard.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.07,0:19:09.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The paint on it had not yet dried.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.87,0:19:11.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was a painting of Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:12.58,0:19:16.96,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So, the painting that Akashi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r} had\Nbeen working on in his room was...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.96,0:19:18.58,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,It was most likely that new portrait.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.71,0:19:24.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The reason why he didn't tell Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}\Nand worked on the painting alone...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.38,0:19:28.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Was because he wanted to complete it\Nbefore Aoi{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-san{\r}'s birthday as a surprise.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.93,0:19:33.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,No, it can't be...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.35,0:19:37.81,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,What have I done...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.10,0:19:40.63,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Ao{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-chan{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.79,0:19:42.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Shuusaku...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.78,0:19:47.20,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Make no intrusion into other's affairs."
Dialogue: 0,0:19:47.99,0:19:54.97,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,When it comes to the relationships between close\Npeople, perhaps outsiders should never interfere.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.83,0:21:22.54,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,All right, Koumei.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:22.54,0:21:23.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You take care of the rest.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:24.79,0:21:29.09,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After all, you did figure out the Red Wall mystery first.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.88,0:21:33.59,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I may not like it, but I'll let you write up the case report.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.18,0:21:36.80,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I knew you would do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:38.81,0:21:43.85,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,You said you had that kid follow me around in order to spy on me...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.40,0:21:50.94,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But let's say that I really was a suspect; it'd still\Nbe too dangerous for him to stay with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.03,0:21:55.41,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Meaning, you never suspected me even from the beginning...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.12,0:21:59.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And instead merely wished for that\Nintelligent child to accompany me, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.87,0:22:03.92,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,As an ally to assist in uncovering the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.92,0:22:06.38,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Hey, hey, he's only a brat.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.88,0:22:10.42,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,After seeing the red wall at the second crime scene...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:10.42,0:22:15.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,We all thought that was a challenge to the police from the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.68,0:22:17.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But only that young man said this:
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.06,0:22:21.99,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But isn't the culprit gonna worry?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.60,0:22:28.49,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Without fully acknowledging the last death scene,\Nthey still tried to imitate the dying message?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.44,0:22:34.70,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it weren't for those words, I doubt we would\Nhave arrived at the truth behind the red wall.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.45,0:22:37.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,The same goes for the evidence's location.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:38.37,0:22:42.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Because the young man mentioned information\Nregarding Lecce, we became enlightened.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:43.83,0:22:47.21,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,So you planned to let me solve the case...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.21,0:22:52.55,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,And take credit for this case so I could return\Nto the Nagano Police Headquarters, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.38,0:22:55.68,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,How unnecessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.18,0:23:01.64,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If our roles were reversed, you'd do the same for me, no?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.48,0:23:05.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,If it were me, I would've done it more discreetly.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:07.10,0:23:09.90,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Not letting you suspect any traces of my plan.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.32,0:23:12.69,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Oh, is that so? I get it!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.69,0:23:14.32,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I'll take credit for this case!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.32,0:23:16.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Stay at that local station forever!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.45,0:23:22.72,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,But, Kansuke{\rHonorifics - Dialogue}-kun{\r}...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:24.16,0:23:28.39,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,I am really grateful to you for letting me meet this boy.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.50,0:23:31.98,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,Thanks to you, I recalled once again...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.67,0:23:38.28,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,From my most favorite book, my most favorite phrase.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.10,0:23:45.87,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"That child carried with him a calm\Nglare that saw through everything...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.48,0:23:50.65,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"And then proceeded to reveal the\Ntruth in a quiet but steady manner.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.77,0:23:56.88,Dialogue,,0,0,0,,"Indeed, just like the famous tactician, Shokatsuryou Koumei."
